race.comment: BREECHES (5) is unlucky to still be a maiden hitting the top-four at her past six starts and strikes a very winnable contest here. Gets in well at the weights with the 1.5kg claim and should be right there when the whips are cracking. MISS COMANECI (7) was a touch disappointing last time out but the form prior was good enough for a race of this nature. Worth another chance. Former Victorian ELLIS BEACH (1) is having his first run for the new stable but should find this task easier than what he faced down south. Keep very safe. THE GENERAL TALKS (4) has been thereabouts in all four runs this preparation and looks a must for the multiples. NATIONAL GOAL (2) will be at peak fitness now fourth-up from the break and may earn some minor money.
